Premier David Makhura says the province will pursue criminal charges. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Special Investigation Unit (SIU) has identified two officials in the Gauteng Department of Health, alleged to be at the centre of PPE tender corruption in the province. READ: Demand for COVID-19 tests dropping in SA: Karim Gauteng Premier David Makhura says one of the officials resigned and criminal charges will be pursued, while the other was suspended. Makhura also says the SIU will conduct lifestyle audits for all MECs in the province, including himself as the Premier. Dan Moyane and @UvekaR with the latest developments from the Gauteng Provincial Command Council, led by Premier David Makhura. #PPECorruption #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/VN0wkL6J02 President Cyril Ramaphosa has appointed several ministers to investigate the alleged looting of millions through dodgy PPE tenders. Makhura was briefing the media on Friday. GAUTENG PROVINCIAL COMMAND COUNCIL Media Briefing Presentation by Premier David Makhura - 7 August 2020 by eNCA.com on Scribd 